name: Devfest 2018 GDG Beni-Suef
description:
Google Developer Group DevFests are the largest Google related events in the world! Each DevFest is carefully crafted for you by your local GDG community to bring in awesome speakers, great topics, and lots fun! While no two events will be exactly alike, each GDG DevFest will, at its core, be powered by a shared belief that when developers come together to exchange ideas, amazing things can happen!

DevFest 2018 GDG Beni-Suefs a 100% community organized full-day developer conference featuring awesome world-class speakers from technology leaders within the community as well as Google product team developers.

name: Cloud Study Jam 2019 GDG/WTM Beni-Suef

venue.name: CodeCaique Solutions
venue.address_1: Kornish Al Nile, Bani Soliman Sharkeya

description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!
Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Creating a VM.
Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want
Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Registration LINK : https://goo.gl/forms/3iNd0lWoW7ZyCM3f2

AGENDA
11:00 am Registration
11:30 am Welcome!
12:00 pm Get free access to Qwiklabs
12:10 pm Lab 1: Introduction to Cloud Computing
12:45 pm : Break
13:00 pm Continue Labs
15:00 pm Break
15:30 pm Competition
16:00 pm Event ends - THANK YOU!

name: Flutter Study Jam 2019 Beni-Suef

venue.name: CodeCaique Solutions
venue.address_1: Kornish Al Nile, Bani Soliman Sharkeya

description:
Join us for a session and workshop in Flutter.
Flutter is Google's mobile app SDK for crafting high-quality native interfaces on iOS and Android with one code & in a record time.

Study Jams are a great opportunity to bring members of your community together to learn Flutter in person and support them to complete the course.

Who can attend?
Flutter Study Jam is best suited for those just getting started with mobile app development or those with programming experience on other mobile app frameworks or anyone with some programming skills and wants to expand his knowledge and keen to learn more.

As always we have swags for the attendees.
- Please bring your laptop for the workshop with Android Studio, or VS Code installed, plus Android SDK is a must to save time.

#flutterextended #GDGBNS #flutterio

name: Hash Code 2019 by Google

venue.name: CodeCaique Solutions
venue.address_1: Kornish Al Nile, Bani Soliman Sharkeya

description:
Hash Code is a team programming competition organized by Google for students and industry professionals across Europe, the Middle East and Africa. You pick your team and programming language, we pick a Google engineering problem for you to solve.

The competition takes place over two rounds:

* Online Qualification Round. Your team can participate from one of our competition hubs or from wherever else you’d like.
Feb 28th, 2019 (19:30 to 23:30)

* Final Round. Top scoring teams from the Online Qualification Round will be invited to Google Dublin to compete in the Final Round of the competition.
* April 27, 2019

Solving past editions' problems is highly recommended:
https://hashcodejudge.withgoogle.com/#/rounds/[masked]/

To register your team (2 - 4 members) per team:
g.co/hashcode

Deadline for registration: 25th February 2019

You can participate from our hub of this year! ;)

After registration you can select our hub: CodeCaique Solutions

from here:
https://hashcodejudge.withgoogle.com/#/my-team

Hub location: CCS. Beni-Suef
On Google Maps : https://goo.gl/maps/kVtQT7NBHLt
